# Tailwind CSS v4 Styling

## General rules

- Use Tailwind utility classes directly on JSX elements — no CSS modules or inline `style` objects except where Tailwind can't reach (e.g. SVG mask tricks, GSAP-set values).
- Respect the design tokens defined in the project: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`, etc. Do not hardcode arbitrary colors.
- Prefer responsive modifiers (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) over duplicating elements per breakpoint.

## Shared CTA variants

Import CTA class strings from `utils/visual`:

```tsx
import { CTA_PRIMARY, CTA_SECONDARY, CTA_TERTIARY } from "utils/visual";

<a className={`hover-scale ${CTA_PRIMARY}`}>…</a>
```

Do not re-define button styles inline.

## Class ordering

Follow Tailwind's recommended class order (layout → box model → typography → visual → interactive). Run `pnpm format` to auto-sort via Prettier plugin.

## Dark mode

The site uses a dark theme by default. Use `text-foreground` / `text-muted` / `bg-background` design tokens. Avoid hardcoded `dark:` variants unless specifically adding light-mode support.
